        <section class="grow" style="background-color:palegreen">
            <h2 style="font-weight:700">Protecting Native Pahadi Cows of Himachal from becoming an Endangered species </h2>
            <p> The trust took an initiative to protect and conserve native cow of Himachal Pradesh which was once abandoned by farmers due to its low productivity. Dealing with the issue the trust started research on how the productivity of this cow can be increased without changes with respect to the quality of milk it yields and after two years of research the native cow was made more productive without compromising on the quality of milk it yields.</p>

        </section>

        <!--Achievement 2-->
        <section class="grow" style="background-color:paleturquoise">

            <h2 style="font-weight:700">Certified Production of the Superior A2 Quality Milk post adequate Efforts and Research. </h2>
            <p> The trust sent the samples of milk yielded by Native cow to “A2   Milk Corporation Raipur, Chhattisgarh” wherein it was certified that the milk so yielded is of A2 quality which is very useful for human health and is beneficial for curing various health ailments.</p>

        </section>

        <!--Achievement 3-->
        <section class="grow" style="background-color:palegreen">
            <h2 style="font-weight:700">Organization of Free Training Sessions for the Local Farmers on the Model of 'Zero Budget Kheti' </h2>
            <p> The trust organised training sessions on “Zero Budget Kheti” to promote the natural way of farming through by products of native cow to eliminate the usage of chemical pesticides and fertilizers. Till now trust had provided training to 150 farmers from nearby villages of Kalyani Gauri (Pahari) Goshala.</p>

        </section>



        <!--Achievement 4-->
        <section class="grow" style="background-color:paleturquoise">
